F(t)=\int_0^t f(s)ds
f
M>0
|F(t)|\leq M|t|
|t|
t
M
f
|f(s)|\le M
s\in \Bbb R
t\ge 0
t\lt 0
\begin{align} |F(t)|&=&\left|\int_0^tf(s)ds\right|\le \int_0^t|f(s)|ds\\&\le& \int_0^tMds=Mt=M|t| \end{align}
\begin{align}|F(t)|&=&\left|\int_0^tf(s)ds\right|=\left|-\int_t^0f(s)ds\right|=\left|\int_t^0f(s)ds\right|\\&\le&\int_t^0|f(s)|ds\le\int_t^0Mds=M(-t)=M|t|\end{align}
